<IMG SRC="g10222.jpg" ALT="GRAPHIC" WIDTH="148" HEIGHT="148">
  </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B>Dear Shareholders:</B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>It
is my pleasure to inform you that our 2014 annual meeting of shareholders will be held at the Hotel du Pont, 11<SUP>th</SUP>&nbsp;and Market Streets, Wilmington, Delaware, on Thursday,
May&nbsp;8, 2014. As we prepare for the annual meeting, it is appropriate to share with you my thoughts on our performance of the past year and our expectations for 2014. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>In
2013, Ford Motor Company continued to go further to meet the needs of our customers, the challenges of our industry and the issues confronting our world. Our efforts produced one of the best
full-year pre-tax operating profits in our history and our fourth consecutive year of pre-tax profit of $8&nbsp;billion or higher. We also produced record Automotive operating-related cash flow. We
will continue upgrading our product line in all our markets
around the world and investing for growth in Asia Pacific. Our European transformation is taking hold, and we are on track to return to profitability in 2015. </FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>2013
also marked several significant milestones for Ford, including Henry Ford's 150<SUP>th</SUP>&nbsp;birthday and the 100<SUP>th</SUP>&nbsp;Anniversary of the moving assembly line, perhaps
his greatest innovation. That innovative spirit continues with our commitment to create a better world through our sustainability goals, such as reducing energy consumption per vehicle produced by 25%
between 2011 and 2016; cutting waste by 40% between 2011 and 2016; reducing water usage by 30% through 2015; and eliminating CO<SUB>2</SUB> emissions by 30% per vehicle between 2010 and 2025. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>A
great standard-bearer of our innovative spirit was my father, William Clay Ford, who passed away on March&nbsp;8, 2014. My father served our Company for 57&nbsp;years as an employee and board
member and eight years as our Director Emeritus. Directly linked to our past, he maintained and strengthened our heritage as a family company while helping to guide us into the modern era. He was a
wonderful father, a great leader and a highly respected man, who will continue to inspire us as we move forward. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Our
plan is to continue serving our customers in all markets around the world with a full family of vehicles&nbsp;&#151; small, medium and large; cars, utilities and
trucks&nbsp;&#151; with the very best quality, fuel efficiency, safety, smart design and value&nbsp;&#151; built on global platforms. This laser-focus will help us toward our goal of
increased global sales and market share, as well as support our ongoing commitment to reducing the environmental impact of our vehicles and operations. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>We
have a great plan and outstanding leadership. Thank you for your continued support. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B>March&nbsp;28, 2014</B></FONT></P>
 <DIV style="padding:0pt;position:relative;width:100%;margin-left:0%;">
<p style="font-family:arial;"></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=5><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=5><B>Thursday, May&nbsp;8, 2014</B></FONT><BR><FONT SIZE=4><B>8:30&nbsp;a.m., Eastern Time<BR>  </B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2><B>Hotel du Pont, 11<SUP>th</SUP>&nbsp;and Market Streets, Wilmington,
Delaware</B></FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>The
annual meeting will begin promptly at 8:30&nbsp;a.m., Eastern Time. If you plan to attend the meeting, please see the instructions on page&nbsp;6 of the attached Proxy Statement. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B>Items of Business:</B></FONT></P>

<DL compact>
<DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>1.</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>The
election of the 16 director nominees named in the Proxy Statement.
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>2.</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>The
ratification of the selection of PricewaterhouseCoopers&nbsp;LLP as Ford's independent registered public accounting firm for 2014.
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>3.</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>A
non-binding shareholder advisory vote to approve the compensation of the Named Executives.
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>4.</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Approval
of the 2014 Stock Plan for Non-Employee Directors.
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>5.</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Consideration
of the two shareholder proposals set forth in the Proxy Statement. </FONT></DD></DL>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>You
can vote if you were a shareholder of record at the close of business on March&nbsp;12, 2014. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Please
read these materials so that you'll know what we plan to do at the meeting. Also, please either sign and return the accompanying proxy card in the postage-paid envelope or instruct us by
telephone or via the Internet as to how you would like your shares voted. This way, your shares will be voted as you direct even if you can't attend the meeting. Instructions on how to vote your
shares by telephone or via the Internet are on the proxy card enclosed with the Proxy Statement. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Shareholders
are being notified of the Proxy Statement and the form of proxy beginning March&nbsp;28, 2014. </FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B>March&nbsp;28, 2014</B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Dearborn,
Michigan </FONT></P>

<P ALIGN="RIGHT" style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B>
<IMG SRC="g932419.jpg" ALT="GRAPHIC" WIDTH="277" HEIGHT="79">
  </B></FONT></P>

<P ALIGN="RIGHT" style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B>Bradley M. Gayton<BR>  </B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2><I>Secretary</I></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>
<!-- BOXING PARAGRAPH(S) -->
 </FONT></P>
<DIV style="width:100%;border:solid #09357A 2pt;margin-right:2pt;padding-top:12pt;padding-right:14pt;padding-bottom:13pt;padding-left:16pt;">


<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>We
urge each shareowner to promptly sign and return the enclosed proxy card or to use telephone or Internet voting. See our questions and answers about the meeting and voting section for information
about voting by telephone or Internet, how to revoke a proxy, and how to vote shares in person. </FONT></P>
 <p style="font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;"></p>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="bf78801_defined_terms"> </A>
<A NAME="toc_bf78801_2"> </A>
<BR></FONT><FONT SIZE=5><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=5><B>Defined Terms    <BR>  </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B><I>"Annual Incentive Compensation Plan"</I></B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> or </FONT><FONT SIZE=2><B><I>"Incentive Bonus Plan"</I></B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> means Ford's Annual Incentive
Compensation Plan. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B><I>"Class&nbsp;B Stock"</I></B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> means Ford's Class&nbsp;B Stock. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B><I>"Deferred Compensation Plan"</I></B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> means Ford's Deferred Compensation Plan. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B><I>"Dividend Equivalent"</I></B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> means cash or shares of common stock (or common stock units) equal in value to dividends, if any, paid on shares of common stock. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B><I>"Final Award"</I></B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> means shares of common stock, Restricted Stock Units, and cash awarded by the Compensation Committee under a Performance Unit. </FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B><I>"Ford"</I></B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> or </FONT><FONT SIZE=2><B><I>"we"</I></B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> or </FONT><FONT SIZE=2><B><I>"Company"</I></B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> means Ford Motor Company. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B><I>"Long-Term Incentive Plan"</I></B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> means Ford's 1998 or 2008 Long-Term Incentive Plan. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B><I>"Named Executives"</I></B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> means the executives named in the Summary Compensation Table on p.&nbsp;64. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B><I>"NYSE"</I></B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> means the New York Stock Exchange&nbsp;LLC. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B><I>"Performance Unit"</I></B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> means, under the Long-Term Incentive Plan, an award of the right to earn up to a certain number of shares of common stock, Restricted
Stock Units, or cash, or a combination of cash and shares of common stock or Restricted Stock Units, based on performance against specified goals established by the Compensation Committee. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B><I>"Restricted Stock Unit"</I></B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> means, under the Long-Term Incentive Plan, the right to receive a share of common stock, or cash equivalent to the value of a
share of common stock, when the restriction period ends, as determined by the Compensation Committee. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B><I>"SEC"</I></B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> means the United States Securities and Exchange Commission. </FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B><I>"Senior Convertible Notes"</I></B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> means the Ford Motor Company 4.25% Senior Convertible Notes due 2036 and the Ford Motor Company 4.25% Senior Convertible
Notes due 2016. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B><I>"1998 Plan"</I></B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> means Ford's 1998 Long-Term Incentive Plan. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B><I>"2008 Plan"</I></B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> means Ford's 2008 Long-Term Incentive Plan. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B><I>"2014 Plan"</I></B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> means the 2014 Stock Plan for Non-Employee Directors of Ford Motor Company. </FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B>ii </B></FONT></P>

<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=5><B>2014 Proxy Statement&nbsp;&#151; Summary</B></FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B>The Board of Directors is soliciting proxies to be used at the annual meeting of shareholders to be held on
Thursday, May&nbsp;8, 2014, beginning at 8:30&nbsp;a.m., Eastern Time, at the Hotel du Pont, 11<SUP>th</SUP>&nbsp;and Market Streets, Wilmington, Delaware. This Proxy Statement and the
enclosed proxy are being made available to shareholders beginning March&nbsp;28, 2014.</B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>This
summary highlights information contained elsewhere in this Proxy Statement. This summary does not contain all of the information you should consider. You should read the entire Proxy Statement
carefully before voting. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=3><B>

 </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="Questions_and_ans"></A> </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="ca78801_questions_and_answers_about_the_proxy_materials"> </A>
<A NAME="toc_ca78801_1"> </A></FONT>
<BR><FONT SIZE=5><B>



<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=5><B>Questions and Answers About the Proxy Materials</B></FONT><FONT SIZE=5><B><BR>      <BR>  </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=3><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=3><B><A NAME="What1"></A>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


WHAT IS A PROXY? WHAT IS A PROXY STATEMENT?<BR>

<!-- COMMAND=ADD_LINERULETXT,NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" -->
<HR NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" >


  </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>A
proxy is another person that you legally designate to vote your stock. If you designate someone as your proxy in a written document, that document also is called a proxy or a proxy card. A proxy
statement is a document that SEC regulations require that we make available to you when we ask you to vote your stock at the annual meeting. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=3><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=3><B><A NAME="What_is_the_purp"></A>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


WHAT IS THE PURPOSE OF THE ANNUAL MEETING?<BR>

<!-- COMMAND=ADD_LINERULETXT,NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" -->
<HR NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" >


  </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>At
our annual meeting, shareholders will act upon the matters outlined in the notice of meeting, including the election of 16 director nominees, ratification of the selection of the Company's
independent registered public accounting firm, a non-binding shareholder advisory vote to approve the compensation of the Named Executives, approval of the 2014 Plan, and consideration of two
shareholder proposals, if presented at the meeting. Also, management will report on the state of the Company and respond to questions from shareholders. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=3><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=3><B><A NAME="What_is_the_re"></A>WHAT IS THE RECORD DATE AND WHAT DOES IT MEAN?<BR>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_LINERULETXT,NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" -->
<HR NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" >


 </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>The
record date for the annual meeting is March&nbsp;12, 2014. The record date is established by the Board of Directors as required by Delaware law. Holders of common stock and holders of
Class&nbsp;B Stock at the close of business on the record date are entitled to receive notice of the meeting and to vote at the meeting and any adjournments or postponements of the meeting. </FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=3><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=3><B><A NAME="who_is_entititeld"></A>WHO IS ENTITLED TO VOTE AT THE ANNUAL MEETING?<BR>

<!-- COMMAND=ADD_LINERULETXT,NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" -->
<HR NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" >


 </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Holders
of common stock and holders of Class&nbsp;B Stock at the close of business on the record date may vote at the meeting. Holders of Senior Convertible Notes cannot vote at this meeting. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>On
March&nbsp;12, 2014, 3,881,659,802&nbsp;shares of common stock and 70,852,076&nbsp;shares of Class&nbsp;B Stock were outstanding and, thus, are eligible to be voted. </FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=3><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=3><B><A NAME="What_are_the_voting"></A>WHAT ARE THE VOTING RIGHTS OF THE HOLDERS OF COMMON STOCK AND CLASS B
STOCK?<BR>

<!-- COMMAND=ADD_LINERULETXT,NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" -->
<HR NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" >


 </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Holders
of common stock and holders of Class&nbsp;B Stock will vote together without regard to class on the matters to be voted upon at the meeting. Holders of common stock have 60% of the general
voting power. Holders of Class&nbsp;B Stock have the remaining 40% of the general voting power. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Each
outstanding share of common stock will be entitled to one vote on each matter to be voted upon. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>The
number of votes for each share of Class&nbsp;B Stock is calculated each year in accordance with the Company's Restated Certificate of Incorporation. At this year's meeting, each outstanding
share of Class&nbsp;B Stock will be entitled to 36.524 votes on each matter to be voted upon. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B>2 </B></FONT></P>

<HR NOSHADE>
<P style='font-family:arial;page-break-before:always'></p>
<!-- ZEQ.=1,SEQ=9,EFW="2218659",CP="FORD MOTOR COMPANY",DN="1",CHK=594084,FOLIO='2',FILE='DISK105:[14ZAI1.14ZAI78801]CA78801A.;73',USER='DSCHWAR',CD='27-MAR-2014;18:22' -->
<A NAME="page_ca78801_1_3"> </A>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B> <A HREF="#bg78801a_main_toc">Table of Contents</A> </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><BR><FONT SIZE=5><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=5><B>Questions and Answers About the Proxy Materials</B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=3><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=3><B><A NAME="what_is_the_diff"></A>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


WHAT IS THE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN A SHAREHOLDER OF RECORD AND A "STREET NAME" HOLDER?<BR>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_LINERULETXT,NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" -->
<HR NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" >


 </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><I>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


 </I></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>Shareholder of Record:</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2>&nbsp;If your shares are registered directly
in your name with Computershare Trust Company, N.A., the Company's stock transfer agent, you are considered the shareholder of record, or a registered holder, with respect to those shares. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><I>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</I></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>Street Name Holder:</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2>&nbsp;If your shares are held in a stock
brokerage account or by a bank or other nominee, you are considered the beneficial owner of these shares, and your shares are held in "street name." </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=3><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=3><B><A NAME="HOw_do_i_vote"></A>HOW DO I VOTE MY SHARES?<BR>

<!-- COMMAND=ADD_LINERULETXT,NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" -->
<HR NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" >


  </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><I>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


 </I></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>Shareholder of Record:</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2>&nbsp;If you are a shareholder of record, you
can give a proxy to be voted at the meeting:</FONT><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT></P>

<DL compact>
<DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>over the telephone; </FONT><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#0035CA" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>using the Internet; or </FONT><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT> <FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#0035CA" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>by mailing in a proxy card. </FONT></DD></DL>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>The
telephone and Internet voting procedures have been set up for your convenience and have been designed to authenticate your identity, to allow you to give voting instructions, and to confirm that
those instructions have been recorded properly. If you are a shareholder of record and you would like to vote by telephone or the Internet, please refer to the specific instructions set forth on the
enclosed proxy card. If you wish to vote using a paper format and you return your signed proxy to us before the annual meeting, we will vote your shares as you direct. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><I>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


 </I></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>Employee Savings Plan
Participant:</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2>&nbsp;If you are a Company employee or retiree participating in either of the Company's Savings and Stock Investment Plan for
Salaried Employees or Tax-Efficient Savings Plan for Hourly Employees, then you may be receiving this material because of shares held for you in those plans. In that case, you may use a proxy card to
instruct the plan trustee on how to vote those shares. The trustee will vote the shares in accordance with your instructions and the terms of the plan. If you hold shares in any of these plans, the
trustee will vote the shares held for you even if you do not direct the trustee how to vote. In these cases, the trustee will vote any shares for which the trustee does not receive instructions in the
same proportion as the trustee votes the shares for which the trustee does receive instructions unless otherwise required by ERISA as determined by the investment manager. To allow sufficient time for
voting by trustees and administrators of the plans, your voting instructions must be received by 11:59&nbsp;p.m., Eastern Time, May&nbsp;5, 2014. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><I>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</I></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>Street Name Holder:</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2>&nbsp;If you hold your shares in "street name,"
you must vote your shares in the manner prescribed by your broker or nominee. Your broker or nominee has enclosed, or explained how you can access, a voting instruction card for you to use in
directing the broker or nominee how to vote your shares. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=3><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=3><B><A NAME="can_i_vote_my_share"></A>CAN I VOTE MY SHARES IN PERSON AT THE ANNUAL MEETING?<BR>

<!-- COMMAND=ADD_LINERULETXT,NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" -->
<HR NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" >


  </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><I>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</I></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>Shareholder of Record:</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2>&nbsp;If you are a shareholder of record, you
may vote your shares at the meeting by completing a ballot at the meeting. Even if you currently plan to attend the meeting, we recommend that you also submit your proxy as described above so that
your vote will be counted if you later decide not to attend the meeting. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><I>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</I></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>Employee Savings Plan Participant:</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2>&nbsp;If you hold shares in
either of the Company's Savings and Stock
Investment Plan for Salaried Employees or Tax-Efficient Savings Plan for Hourly Employees, you cannot vote at the meeting. Your shares will be voted by the trustee of those plans as described above. </FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><I>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


 </I></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>Street Name Holder:</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2>&nbsp;If you are a "street name" holder, you may
vote your shares in person only if you obtain a signed proxy from your broker or nominee giving you the right to vote the shares. </FONT></P>

<P ALIGN="RIGHT" style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B>3 </B></FONT></P>

<HR NOSHADE>
<P style='font-family:arial;page-break-before:always'></p>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><BR><FONT SIZE=5><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=5><B>Questions and Answers About the Proxy Materials</B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=3><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=3><B><A NAME="Are_votes_confid"></A>ARE VOTES CONFIDENTIAL? WHO COUNTS THE VOTES?<BR>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_LINERULETXT,NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" -->
<HR NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" >


 </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>The
votes of all shareholders will be held in confidence from directors, officers, and employees of the Company except: (a)&nbsp;as necessary to meet applicable legal requirements and to assert or
defend claims for or against the Company; (b)&nbsp;in case of a contested proxy solicitation; or (c)&nbsp;if a shareholder makes a written comment on the proxy card or otherwise communicates his
or her vote to management. We will also continue, as we have for many years, to retain an independent tabulator to receive and tabulate the proxies and independent inspectors of election to certify
the results. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=3><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->

  </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Proposals&nbsp;1, 2, 3, and 4 will be presented at the meeting by management, and the rest are expected to be presented by
shareholders. </FONT></P>

 <P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=3><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=3><B><A NAME="what_if_I_do_not_sp"></A>WHAT IF I DO NOT SPECIFY HOW I WANT MY SHARES VOTED?<BR>

<!-- COMMAND=ADD_LINERULETXT,NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" -->
<HR NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" >


  </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>If
you do not specify on your proxy card (or when giving your proxy by telephone or the Internet) how you want to vote your shares, we will vote them: </FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><B>FOR</B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> all of the director nominees (Proposal&nbsp;1); </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><B>FOR</B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> ratifying the selection of PricewaterhouseCoopers&nbsp;LLP as the
Company's independent registered public accounting firm for 2014 (Proposal&nbsp;2); </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><B>FOR,</B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> on an advisory basis, approval of the compensation of the Named
Executives (Proposal&nbsp;3); </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><B>FOR</B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> approval of the 2014 Stock Plan for Non-Employee Directors
(Proposal&nbsp;4); and </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><B>AGAINST</B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> the shareholder proposals (Proposals&nbsp;5 and 6). </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=3><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=3><B><A NAME="can_I_change_my_vote"></A>CAN I CHANGE MY VOTE?<BR>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_LINERULETXT,NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" -->
<HR NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" >


 </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Yes.
You can revoke your proxy at any time before it is exercised in any of three ways:</FONT><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT></P>

<DL compact>
<DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>by submitting written notice of revocation to the Secretary of the Company; </FONT><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#0035CA" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>by submitting another proxy by telephone, via the Internet or by mail that is later dated and, if by mail, that is
properly signed; or </FONT><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT> <FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#0035CA" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>if you are a shareholder of record or a "street name" holder, by voting in person at the meeting. </FONT></DD></DL>
<P ALIGN="RIGHT" style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B>5 </B></FONT></P>

<HR NOSHADE>
<P style='font-family:arial;page-break-before:always'></p>
<!-- ZEQ.=4,SEQ=12,EFW="2218659",CP="FORD MOTOR COMPANY",DN="1",CHK=600547,FOLIO='5',FILE='DISK105:[14ZAI1.14ZAI78801]CA78801A.;73',USER='DSCHWAR',CD='27-MAR-2014;18:22' -->
<A NAME="page_ca78801_1_6"> </A>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B> <A HREF="#bg78801a_main_toc">Table of Contents</A> </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><BR><FONT SIZE=5><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=5><B>Questions and Answers About the Proxy Materials</B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=3><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=3><B><A NAME="what_percentage_ofthev"></A>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


WHAT PERCENTAGE OF THE VOTE IS REQUIRED FOR A PROPOSAL TO BE APPROVED?<BR>

<!-- COMMAND=ADD_LINERULETXT,NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" -->
<HR NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" >


 </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>A
majority of the votes that could be cast by shareholders who are either present in person or represented by proxy at the meeting is required to elect the nominees for director and to approve each
proposal. The votes are computed for each share as described on p.&nbsp;2. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>The
total number of votes that could be cast at the meeting is the number of votes actually cast plus the number of abstentions. Abstentions are counted as "shares present" at the meeting for purposes
of determining whether a quorum exists and have the effect of a vote "against" any matter as to which they are specified. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Proxies
submitted by brokers that do not indicate a vote for some or all of the proposals because they don't have discretionary voting authority and haven't received instructions as to how to vote on
those proposals (so-called "broker non-votes") are not considered "shares present" and will not affect the outcome of the vote. </FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=3><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=3><B><A NAME="how_can_I_attend"></A>HOW CAN I ATTEND THE ANNUAL MEETING?<BR>

<!-- COMMAND=ADD_LINERULETXT,NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" -->
<HR NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" >


 </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><I>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</I></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>Shareholder of Record:</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2>&nbsp;If you plan to attend the annual
meeting, please let us know by indicating so when you vote your shares. If you received a proxy card in the mail, please tear off the top portion where indicated and bring it with you to the meeting.
If you received a Notice of Annual Meeting and vote your shares via the Internet, please print your ticket from the voting website. This portion of the card will serve as your ticket and will admit
you and one guest. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><I>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</I></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>Street Name Holder:</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2>&nbsp;If you plan to attend the annual meeting,
tell your broker or nominee that you are planning to attend the meeting and would like a legal proxy. Then simply bring that form to the meeting and we'll give you a ticket at the door that will admit
you and one guest. If you can't get a legal proxy in time, we can still give you a ticket at the door if you bring a copy of your brokerage account statement showing that you owned Ford stock as of
the record date, March&nbsp;12, 2014. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=3><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=3><B><A NAME="Are_there_any_rules"></A>ARE THERE ANY RULES REGARDING ADMISSION?<BR>

<!-- COMMAND=ADD_LINERULETXT,NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" -->
<HR NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" >


  </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Each
shareholder and guest will be asked to present valid government-issued picture identification, such as a driver's license or passport, before being admitted to the meeting. Cameras and audio and
video recording devices will not be permitted at the meeting and attendees will be subject to security inspections. We encourage you to leave any such items at home. We will not be responsible for any
items checked at the door. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=3><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=3><B><A NAME="Are_there_any_other_matts"></A>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


ARE THERE ANY OTHER MATTERS TO BE ACTED UPON AT THE ANNUAL MEETING?<BR>

<!-- COMMAND=ADD_LINERULETXT,NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" -->
<HR NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" >


  </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>We
do not know of any other matters to be presented or acted upon at the meeting. Under our By-Laws, no business besides that stated in the meeting notice may be transacted at any meeting of
shareholders. If any other matter is presented at the meeting on which a vote may properly be taken, the shares represented by proxies will be voted in accordance with the judgment of the person or
persons voting those shares. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B>6 </B></FONT></P>

<HR NOSHADE>
<P style='font-family:arial;page-break-before:always'></p>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><BR><FONT SIZE=5><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=5><B>Questions and Answers About the Proxy Materials</B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=3><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=3><B><A NAME="electronic_access_to_prox"></A>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


ELECTRONIC ACCESS TO PROXY MATERIALS AND ANNUAL REPORT<BR>

<!-- COMMAND=ADD_LINERULETXT,NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" -->
<HR NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" >


  </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>This
Proxy Statement and our 2013 Annual Report are available on our website at <U>www.corporate.ford.com</U>. Instead of receiving paper copies of next year's Proxy Statement
and Annual Report by mail, you can elect to receive an e-mail message that will provide a link to those documents on the Internet. By opting to access your proxy materials via the Internet, you
will:</FONT><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT></P>

<DL compact>
<DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Gain faster access to your proxy materials; </FONT><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#0035CA" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Save us the cost of producing and mailing documents to you; </FONT><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT> <FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#0035CA" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Reduce the amount of mail you receive; and </FONT><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#0035CA" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Help preserve environmental resources. </FONT></DD></DL>


<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Ford
shareholders who have enrolled in the electronic access service previously will receive their materials online this year. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Shareholders
of record may enroll in the electronic proxy and Annual Report access service for future Annual Meetings of Shareholders by registering online at
<U>www.eTree.com/ford</U>. During 2013, 3,980 trees were planted as a result of shareholders enrolling in the electronic delivery program. Experts say 3,980 mature trees absorb 1
million pounds of CO<SUB>2</SUB> annually and produce enough oxygen to support 8,000 humans. If you vote via the Internet, simply follow the prompts that will link you to that website. "Street name"
shareholders who wish to enroll for electronic access may register for online delivery of materials by going to <U>www.icsdelivery.com/live</U>. </FONT></P>

</FONT> <FONT SIZE=2><A HREF="#bg78801a_main_toc">Table of Contents</A> </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="Corp_govern"></A></FONT><FONT SIZE=5><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=5><B>Corporate Governance</B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=5><B> <A NAME="Corp_Govern_PRinc"></A>  </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=3><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=3><B>Corporate Governance Principles<BR>

<!-- COMMAND=ADD_LINERULETXT,NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" -->
<HR NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" >


  </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>The
Nominating and Governance Committee developed and recommended to the Board a set of corporate governance principles, which the Board adopted. Ford's Corporate Governance Principles may be found on
its website at <U>www.corporate.ford.com</U>. These principles include: a limitation on the number of boards on which a director may serve, qualifications for directors
(including a requirement that directors be prepared to resign from the Board in the event of any significant change in their personal circumstances that could affect the discharge of their
responsibilities), director orientation, continuing education and a requirement that the Board and each of its Committees perform an annual self-evaluation. Shareholders may obtain a printed copy of
the Company's Corporate Governance Principles by writing to our Shareholder Relations Department, Ford Motor Company, One American Road, Suite&nbsp;1026, Dearborn, Michigan 48126-2798. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="Corp_Govern_PRac"></A> </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=3><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=3><B>Corporate Governance Practices<BR>

<!-- COMMAND=ADD_LINERULETXT,NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" -->
<HR NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" >


  </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Ford
has a long history of operating under sound corporate governance practices, which is a critical element of our success in delivering our ONE Ford Plan, and creating profitable growth for all. The
Board continuously reviews our governance practices, assesses the regulatory and legislative environment, and adopts governance practices that best serve the interest of Ford's stockholders
including:</FONT><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT></P>

<DL compact>
<DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>Annual Election of All
Directors.</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2>



<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT> <FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#0035CA" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT> <FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>Majority Vote Standard.</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> Each director must be
elected by a majority of votes cast. </FONT><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#0035CA" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>Independent Board.</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> Our Board is comprised of 82%
independent directors. </FONT><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT> <FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#0035CA" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>Presiding Independent Director.</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> Ensures management
is adequately addressing the matters identified by the Board.</FONT><FONT SIZE=2>



<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT> <FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#0035CA" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT> <FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>Independent Board Committees.</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> Each of the Audit,
Compensation, and Nominating and Governance committees is comprised of independent directors. </FONT><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#0035CA" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>



<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT> <FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>Committee Charters.</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> Each standing committee
operates under a written charter that has been approved by the Board. </FONT><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT> <FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#0035CA" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>Independent Directors Meet Regularly Without Management, and Non-Independent
Directors.</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT> <FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#0035CA" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT> <FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>Regular Board and Committee Self-Evaluation
Process.</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> The Board and each committee evaluates its performance each year. </FONT><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#0035CA" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>Mandatory Deferral of Compensation for Directors.</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2>
60% of annual director fees are mandatorily deferred into Ford common stock units until retirement, which strongly links the interests of the Board with those of shareholders. </FONT><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#0035CA" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>Separate Chairman of the Board and CEO.</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> The Board
of Directors has chosen to separate the roles of CEO and Chairman of the Board of Directors. </FONT><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT> <FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#0035CA" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>Stock Ownership Goals for Executives.</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> Significant
stock ownership objectives strongly link the interests of management with those of stockholders. </FONT><FONT SIZE=2>



<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT> <FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#0035CA" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT> <FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>Recoupment Policy.</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> The Compensation Committee
adopted a policy of recoupment of executive compensation in certain circumstances. </FONT><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#0035CA" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>



<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT> <FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>No Change-in-Control
Agreements.</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT> <FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#0035CA" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>Confidential Voting.</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2>



<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT> <FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#0035CA" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT> <FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>Special Meetings.</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> Shareholders have the right to
call a special meeting. </FONT><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#0035CA" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>



<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT> <FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>Shareholders May Take Action by Written
Consent.</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT> <FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#0035CA" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2><I>Strong Codes of Ethics.</I></FONT><FONT SIZE=2> Ford is committed to
operating its business with the highest level of integrity and has adopted codes of ethics that apply to all employees, as well as the Board of Directors. </FONT></DD></DL>


<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B>8 </B></FONT></P>

<HR NOSHADE>
<P style='font-family:arial;page-break-before:always'></p>
<!-- ZEQ.=1,SEQ=15,EFW="2218659",CP="FORD MOTOR COMPANY",DN="1",CHK=340118,FOLIO='8',FILE='DISK105:[14ZAI1.14ZAI78801]CE78801A.;69',USER='KBLACK',CD='22-MAR-2014;19:31' -->
<A NAME="page_ce78801_1_9"> </A>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B> <A HREF="#bg78801a_main_toc">Table of Contents</A> </B></FONT></P>

<UL>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="leadership_struc"></A> </FONT></P>

</UL>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=3><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=3><B>Leadership Structure<BR>

<!-- COMMAND=ADD_LINERULETXT,NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" -->
<HR NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" >


  </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Ford
determines the most suitable leadership structure from time to time. At present, the Board of Directors has chosen to separate the roles of CEO and Chairman of the Board of Directors. Alan
Mulally is our President and CEO and William Clay Ford,&nbsp;Jr., is Chairman of the Board of Directors as well as our Executive Chairman. We believe this structure is optimal for Ford at this time
because it allows Mr.&nbsp;Mulally to focus on strategy and the implementation of our ONE Ford Plan, while allowing Mr.&nbsp;Ford to focus on leadership of the Board of Directors in addition to
providing the Company with direction on Company-wide issues such as sustainability, personal mobility, and stakeholder relationships. Furthermore, the Board has appointed Ellen&nbsp;R. Marram as our
Presiding Independent Director. We believe having a Presiding Independent Director is an important governance practice given that the Chairman of the Board, Mr.&nbsp;Ford, is not an independent
director under our Corporate Governance Principles. The duties of the Presiding Independent Director include:</FONT><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT></P>

<DL compact>
<DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>chairing the executive sessions of our independent directors; </FONT><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#0035CA" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>advising on the selection of Board Committee Chairs; and </FONT><FONT SIZE=2>



<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


</FONT> <FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT COLOR="#0035CA" SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>working with Mr.&nbsp;Ford and Mr.&nbsp;Mulally to ensure management is adequately addressing the matters identified
by the Board. </FONT></DD></DL>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>This
structure optimizes the roles of CEO, Chairman, and the Presiding Independent Director and provides Ford with sound corporate governance in the management of its business. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="Board_meetings_comp"></A> </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=3><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS294" -->


 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#09357A" SIZE=3><B>Board Meetings, Composition&nbsp;and Committees<BR>

<!-- COMMAND=ADD_LINERULETXT,NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" -->
<HR NOSHADE  COLOR="#000000" SIZE="1.0PT" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="LEFT" >


 </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B> Executive Sessions of Non-Employee Directors  </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Non-employee directors ordinarily meet in executive session without management present at most regularly scheduled Board meetings and may meet at
other times at the discretion of the Presiding Independent Director or at the request of any non-employee director. Additionally, all of the independent directors meet periodically (at least annually)
without management or non-independent directors present. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B> Composition of Board of Directors/Nominees  </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>The Nominating and Governance Committee recommends the nominees for all directorships. The Committee also reviews and makes recommendations to the
Board on matters such as the size and composition of the Board in order to ensure the Board has the requisite expertise and its membership consists of persons with sufficiently diverse and independent
backgrounds. Between annual shareholder meetings, the Board may elect directors to vacant Board positions to serve until the next annual meeting. </FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>In
2013, the Committee recommended that the size of the Board be expanded to seventeen directors given that certain directors are approaching, or have exceeded, the mandatory retirement age contained
in our Corporate Governance Principles. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>The
Committee considers an appropriate mix of long-, medium-, and short-term tenured directors in its succession planning, particularly when it considers waiving the mandatory retirement age for
directors. Although Mr.&nbsp;Gephardt has reached the retirement age of 72&nbsp;years, the Board has waived the retirement age for him as permitted under our Corporate Governance Principles so
that it may continue to avail itself of Mr.&nbsp;Gephardt's expertise in governmental relations matters, and to manage the succession planning of the Board's membership. </FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>The
Board believes that it has an appropriate mix of short- to medium-tenured directors as well as long-tenured directors that provide an excellent balance that enables the Board to benefit from fresh
insights and historical perspective during its deliberations. In addition, the Board has managed succession planning effectively with strategic waivers of the mandatory retirement age where
appropriate to maintain certain </FONT></P>

<P ALIGN="RIGHT" style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B>9 </B></FONT></P>

<HR NOSHADE>
<P style='font-family:arial;page-break-before:always'></p>
<!-- ZEQ.=2,SEQ=16,EFW="2218659",CP="FORD MOTOR COMPANY",DN="1",CHK=85275,FOLIO='9',FILE='DISK105:[14ZAI1.14ZAI78801]CE78801A.;69',USER='KBLACK',CD='22-MAR-2014;19:31' -->
<A NAME="page_ce78801_1_10"> </A>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B> <A HREF="#bg78801a_main_toc">Table of Contents</A> </B></FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>expertise
while new directors supplement the Board structure. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>The
Board proposes to you a slate of nominees for election to the Board at the annual meeting. You may propose nominees (other than self-nominations) for consideration by the Committee by submitting
the names, qualifications and other supporting information to: Secretary, Ford Motor Company, One American Road, Dearborn, MI 48126. Properly submitted recommendations must be received no later than
November&nbsp;28, 2014 to be considered by the Committee for inclusion in the following year's nominations for election to the Board. Your properly submitted candidates are evaluated in the same
manner as those candidates recommended by other sources. All candidates are considered in light of the needs of the Board with due consideration given to the qualifications described on p.&nbsp;25
under Election of Directors. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B> Board Committees  </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Only independent directors serve on the Audit, Compensation, and Nominating and Governance Committees, in accordance with the independence standards
of the NYSE Listed Company rules and the Company's Corporate Governance Principles. The Board, and each committee of the Board, has the authority to engage independent consultants and advisors at the
Company's expense. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>The
Company has published on its website (<U>www.corporate.ford.com</U>) the charter of each of the Audit, Compensation, Finance, Nominating and Governance, and Sustainability
Committees of the Board. Printed copies of each of the committee charters are available by writing to our Shareholder Relations Department, Ford Motor Company, One American Road, Suite&nbsp;1026,
Dearborn, Michigan 48126-2798. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B> Board Committee Membership  </B></FONT></P>

<p style="font-family:arial;"></FONT></P>

 <P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B>I&nbsp;</B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2>Indicates Independent Director&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT> <FONT SIZE=2><B>C</B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2>&nbsp;Indicates Chair of Committee&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT> <FONT
